      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to knock the recent consistency of PERFECT STRANGER NZ (2) who got within 3m of boom colt Hollywood Strip two back then led from wider than this and went on to score by 4.2m at this circuit and distance last week. Has the speed to take advantage of the ace draw so can strike again. MAJOR ART NZ (7) is finding it hard to break through but has managed to finish second in all four starts since arriving from NZ, missing by narrow margins at his last three. Edged out by a nose from a similar draw at this circuit and distance last week. Could break through. DANCE WITH CARMER (11) worked from this barrier but toughed out a narrow win over Major Art last week. Could back that up. HUGO MAGUIRE NZ (5) has the hoof on the till after placing in his last three outings while a good draws can see LENNETH (4) competitive again.",
